@NODE 1. "Introduction"

I'll bet, like most who have learned to use the InterNet, you too love the
InterNet. Although it has many advantages, it also has its drawbacks. One of
these disadvantages is the fact that sometimes the meaning of a sentence is not
quite clear, for example: 'You again...' may be implied in a derogatory or
ironic way. This is generally where the so-called "smiley" gets used. However,
depending on the font you use, smileys sometimes look very ugly. :( Sometimes
the ':' is too high or the ')' is too low, or the proportions may even be
wrong. Now, however, there are the 'SmileFonts'! This font is based upon the
well known Helvetica font, but I have optimised it for using smileys. I have
altered the fonts to make smileys look good, while maintaining their usefulness
under "normal" circumstances. I think I was quite sucessful... If you have any
suggetions, please let me know! I hope you can make good use of these fonts. I
hope to hear from you! 'Til then...KEEP SMILING :-)

BTW, since I only access the InterNet via a Unix terminal, I would greatly
appreciate it if someone could convert these fonts to Unix format 8^) (no joke).


@ENDNODE

