@NODE 4. "Specials"

Here are some smiley-parts which are activated through special keys and look
almost as good as the originals (Note: the following apply for use with
American keymaps; for other countries, the ASCII values are included):

- Ţ  SHIFT RALT t [222]
- ´  ALT f (->SPACE) [180]
- ¬  SHIFT ALT z [172]
- ¦  ALT SHIFT i [166]
- ˘  ALT 4 [162] (*)
- ř  ALT o [248] (*)
- ¸  ALT m [184] (not very 'compatible')

Furthermore some other chars, which can´t all be listed here, have been altered
in size an position. A little bit special is the ´$´...

The following smileys should be tested right away:

- :-(` Have a look at this sadness (discovered by 'Koto')
- 8-(` Seems to look funny, said 'joker'
- ¦8-Ţ My Champion, the best there ever was :)

Known bugs:

Unfortunately I can't claim these fonts to be bugfree. SmileHelvetica seems
not to work with 'Grapevine,' however, the original Helvetica also has this
problem. Futhermore, the so-called (at least by me ;) Gutgolf-smileys are not
displayed correctely (ie. ';c)',';o)' and so on...). I regret that this cannot
be changed as it would result in further incompatibilities :( It is for this
reason that I added the (*)-marked chars. They should provide a good alternative
(I hope)...


@ENDNODE

