@NODE 7. "Risks & SideEffects"

Regular use of SmileFonts very seldom results in spontane laughter followed by
the user rolling on the flor.
In some experiments with betatesters the so-called Smiley-Syndrom appeared,
which let´s people invent more and more ´unbelievable´ kinds of smileys (e.g.
Markus L.).
If during the usage of SmileFonts others than these sideeffects should show up,
please inform your root or administrator.


@ENDNODE

